28/02/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Visiting US Deputy Assistant Secretary of State Thomas Countryman said on Sunday (February 27th) that Washington wants to see a stable and prosperous BiH -- with two strong entities and an efficient state-level government -- progress towards EU integration. He also stressed the importance of respecting the Dayton Peace Agreement. In an interview with the Nezavisne Novine daily, he said the US administration expects the Office of the High Representative to close as soon as conditions for that are met. (Nezavisne Novine, RTRS, Srna - 27/02/11)
